## **ðŸ“š Essential C++ Documentation Resources**

### **Official Resources**
1. **cppreference.com** - https://en.cppreference.com/
   - Most comprehensive C++ reference
   - Covers C++11 through C++23

2. **ISO C++ Official Site** - https://isocpp.org/
   - Official C++ standards information
   - FAQ and guidelines

3. **C++ Core Guidelines** - https://isocpp.github.io/CppCoreGuidelines/CppCoreGuidelines
   - Best practices by Bjarne Stroustrup and Herb Sutter

4. **C++ Standard Draft** - https://eel.is/c++draft/
   - Latest working draft of the standard

### **Learning Resources**
1. **LearnCpp.com** - https://www.learncpp.com/
   - Comprehensive tutorials

2. **Design Patterns** - https://refactoring.guru/design-patterns/cpp
   - Gang of Four patterns with C++ examples

3. **Compiler Explorer** - https://godbolt.org/
   - Online compiler for testing

---

This table covers **every single topic** from all three courses with complete documentation links!
  
